        <chapter>
            <title>Shanghai gold fixing process</title>
            <paragraph>
              The SGE Members offers market reference quotation. If you have +50% offers of prices
              the SGE discard the highest and lowest price and calculates the arithmetic mean. If you
              haven't valid price, the price from the previous trading session should be set as
              the initial price for the current session. If you have -50% offers of prices,
              the SGE will compute the arithmetic mean of all the executed prices for spot gold. Then, the initiale price
              is published.</paragraph> <paragraph>All partecipants submit buying volumes and salling volumes
              based on initial price. Fixing Members submit offering against the imbalanced. If imbalace isn't within
              400 kg it starts from the initial price.</paragraph> <paragraph>Finally, if buying are bigger then selling,
              SGE adjusted the price upward until the buying volume decreases and selling one increases.
              If buying are smaller then selling, SGE adjusted the price ownward until
              the buying volume increases and selling one decreases. After adjustments, price is published.</paragraph>
        </chapter>
